The paper deals with clustering of data points, which is a fundamental tool in data analysis, and discusses efficient constructions of small samples that act as surrogates to the full data for performing clustering tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories of arXiv CS.
